bug.short_desc: The configuration key "members" in class "..." is not allowed!

long_desc.thetext:
I get the following error message: The configuration key "members" in class "...EventBus" is not allowed! Line 805 of qooxdoo-1.0-sdk/framework/source/class/qx/Class.js
This error message can be fixed by adding the following line of code to the class "...EventBus": extend : qx.core.Object,
If the missing extend-statement is the problem, why does the error message not say that the extend statement is missing, but gives an error message which makes it hard to find the reason for the problem?
I could add "extend qx.core.Object" to the classes, but then I get another problem: When I run the API-Generator for my project, the generated API alway includes "qx.core.Object" (see attached screenshot), even if the config file looks like this: "API_INCLUDE" : [ "com.unitedinternet.appsengine.frontend.rest.RestCall", "com.unitedinternet.appsengine.frontend.EventBus"], "API_EXCLUDE" : ["qx.*"]

The first part of the report is about more precise error messages, also see bug #1433.
The second part is about excluding certain API namespaces. @Thomas, please have a look.

> When I run the API-Generator for my project, the generated API alway includes > "qx.core.Object" > (see attached screenshot), > even if the config file looks like this: > "API_INCLUDE" : [ "com.unitedinternet.appsengine.frontend.rest.RestCall", > "com.unitedinternet.appsengine.frontend.EventBus"], > "API_EXCLUDE" : ["qx.*"]
Independent of API_EXCLUDE classes are included in the Api viewer that are super-classes of included classes, as otherwise the inheritance hierarchy couldn't be displayed correctly.
BTW: You shouldn't put two issues into the same bug.
This bug can be closed. The bug got obsolete, because this bug report is 6 months old and meanwhile we have several times upgraded to new qooxdoo versions.
